claims:
Claims Claims  What is claimed is: 1. A hemostasis device, comprising: a cuff member for attachment to a patient's hand; and a pressure application device for positioning between the cuff member and the patient's hand, over a site in an anatomical snuff box region of the patient's hand. 2. The hemostasis device according to claim 1, wherein said cuff member wraps around the patient's hand and encapsulates the patient's thumb. 3. The hemostasis device according to claim 2 wherein said cuff member is substantially rigid. 4. The hemostasis device according to claim 2 wherein said cuff member holds said pressure application device in position to maintain a pressure applied to the snuff box region of the patient's hand. 5. The hemostasis device according to claim 1, wherein said pressure application device comprises an inflatable member adapted to press against the patient when inflated. 6. The hemostasis device according to claim 5 wherein said cuff member and said pressure application device respectively include a substantially clear viewing portion for enabling viewing of the position on the patient where said inflatable member presses when inflated. 7. The hemostasis device according to claim 5 wherein said inflatable member includes an inflation port to enable attachment of an inflation source. 8. The hemostasis device according to claim 7 further comprising a valve for preventing unintended release of pressure from the inflation member. 9. The hemostasis device according to claim 1, said pressure application device further comprises a receptacle for holding a substance wherein the substance is dispensed to the patient by pressure provided by the pressure application device. 10. The hemostasis device according to claim 9, wherein said substance comprises a hemostatic substance . 11. A hemostasis device, comprising: a cuff for fitting onto a patient's hand; and a pressure application member positionable between the patient's hand and a puncture site to apply pressure against the puncture site. 12. The hemostasis device according to claim 11, wherein a the pressure application member comprises an inflatable member. 13. The hemostasis device according to claim 11, wherein the cuff includes a thumb opening for fitting the patient's thumb therethrough. 14. The hemostasis device according to claim 11, 

comprising a securement member for securing the cuff to the patient's hand. 15. The hemostasis device according to claim 11, wherein the cuff includes at least a portion that is see-through to allow viewing of the positioning of pressure application member. 16. The hemostasis device according to claim 12, wherein the inflatable member includes at least a portion that is see-through to allow viewing of the puncture site through the pressure application member. 17. The hemostasis device according to claim 11, wherein the cuff and the pressure application member include at least portions that are see-through to allow viewing of the positioning of pressure application member relative to the puncture site. 18. The hemostasis device according to claim 11 wherein at least a portion of said cuff is substantially rigid. 19. A method of accomplishing hemostasis in a snuff box region of a patient after a radial artery access procedure, comprising: providing at least partially rigid cuff member to a hand of the patient; providing an inflation bubble for positioning between at a rigid portion of the cuff member and the patient's hand; positioning the inflation bubble over a puncture site in the snuff box region on the patient's hand; and; 

 inflating the inflation bubble to apply pressure between the patient's hand and the cuff member. 20. The method according to claim 19, wherein said cuff member and said inflation bubble provide a viewing area for observation of a puncture site on the patient's hand.
